---
description: Keep git commits attributed to the human developer for GitHub contributions.
alwaysApply: true
---

When creating git commits in this repository:

- Do not add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Made-with: Cursor`, or any Cursor/agent attribution trailers.
- Do not pass `--trailer` flags that add Cursor as co-author.
- Use only the human author's commit message (subject and body).
- Always commit with the verified GitHub identity so contributions count on the profile:
  `git -c user.name="Mohammad Anwar Attar" -c user.email="mohd13adnan15@gmail.com" commit ...`
  Do not use `www.adi15042006@gmail.com` — that email is not linked to the GitHub account.

The repository uses a `prepare-commit-msg` hook that strips Cursor co-author lines if they are added accidentally.
